<figureCitation id="98F21AC48F1AFE944A775693FD40FE27" box="[583,741,447,471]" captionStart="PLATE 100" captionStartId="338.[151,233,1962,1985]" captionTargetBox="[182,1424,186,1921]" captionTargetId="figure-56@338.[151,1436,163,1977]" captionTargetPageId="338" captionText="PLATE 100. Echthrodelphax fairchildii. A, B. Female in dorsal view (A) and lateral view (B). Length 2.5 mm. C. Chela of female from Japan. Scale bar 0.16 mm for C. (From Olmi 1984)" figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5278728" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5278728/files/figure.png" pageId="340" pageNumber="341">Plate 100A, B</figureCitation>
); rarely brachypterous (only in 
<specimenCount id="16CFCDC88F1AFE944C7756ECFB7AFE27" box="[1095,1247,447,471]" pageId="340" pageNumber="341" type="generic">one specimen</specimenCount>
of 
<taxonomicName id="C7C97DC28F1AFE944D3456EDFA39FE27" authority="Olmi" authorityName="Olmi 1984:" authorityYear="1157" box="[1284,1436,447,472]" class="Insecta" family="Dryinidae" genus="Echthrodelphax" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="340" pageNumber="341" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="rufus">
<emphasis id="32BDDA538F1AFE944D3456EDFAF9FE28" box="[1284,1372,448,472]" italics="true" pageId="340" pageNumber="341">E. rufus</emphasis>
Olmi
</taxonomicName>
from 
<collectingCountry id="78DE46D18F1AFE9448EA56C8FE85FE0C" box="[218,288,484,508]" name="China" pageId="340" pageNumber="341">China</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingRegion id="C20DC8A38F1AFE94490156C8FE13FE0C" box="[305,438,484,508]" country="China" name="Guangdong" pageId="340" pageNumber="341">Guangdong</collectingRegion>
, Yunjishan Nature Reserve); palpal formula 3/2, 4/2, 5/2, 5/3, or 6/3; antenna with rhinaria; pronotum crossed by strong transverse furrow (
<figureCitation id="98F21AC48F1AFE944B3D552BFC2FFDEF" box="[781,906,519,543]" captionStart="PLATE 100" captionStartId="338.[151,233,1962,1985]" captionTargetBox="[182,1424,186,1921]" captionTargetId="figure-56@338.[151,1436,163,1977]" captionTargetPageId="338" captionText="PLATE 100. Echthrodelphax fairchildii. A, B. Female in dorsal view (A) and lateral view (B). Length 2.5 mm. C. Chela of female from Japan. Scale bar 0.16 mm for C. (From Olmi 1984)" figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5278728" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5278728/files/figure.png" pageId="340" pageNumber="341">Plate 100A</figureCitation>
); notauli complete (
<figureCitation id="98F21AC48F1AFE944C5C552BFB4CFDEF" box="[1132,1257,519,543]" captionStart="PLATE 100" captionStartId="338.[151,233,1962,1985]" captionTargetBox="[182,1424,186,1921]" captionTargetId="figure-56@338.[151,1436,163,1977]" captionTargetPageId="338" captionText="PLATE 100. Echthrodelphax fairchildii. A, B. Female in dorsal view (A) and lateral view (B). Length 2.5 mm. C. Chela of female from Japan. Scale bar 0.16 mm for C. (From Olmi 1984)" figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5278728" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5278728/files/figure.png" pageId="340" pageNumber="341">Plate 100A</figureCitation>
); enlarged claw with one subapical tooth and one row of lamellae (
<figureCitation id="98F21AC48F1AFE944AFF5500FCF0FDB4" box="[719,853,556,580]" captionStart="PLATE 100" captionStartId="338.[151,233,1962,1985]" captionTargetBox="[182,1424,186,1921]" captionTargetId="figure-56@338.[151,1436,163,1977]" captionTargetPageId="338" captionText="PLATE 100. Echthrodelphax fairchildii. A, B. Female in dorsal view (A) and lateral view (B). Length 2.5 mm. C. Chela of female from Japan. Scale bar 0.16 mm for C. (From Olmi 1984)" figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5278728" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5278728/files/figure.png" pageId="340" pageNumber="341">Plates 100C</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="98F21AC48F1AFE944B535500FC67FDB3" box="[867,962,556,580]" captionStart="PLATE 102" captionStartId="343.[151,234,1877,1900]" captionTargetBox="[220,1315,217,1819]" captionTargetId="figure-107@343.[166,1421,193,1856]" captionTargetPageId="343" captionText="PLATE 102. A, B, E, F. Male genitalia. C, D. Chelae. A. Echthrodelphax fairchildii from Hawaii (from Olmi 1984). B, C. E. laotianus from Thailand (from Olmi 1998e). C. E. laotianus, holotype (from Olmi 1984). D. E. rufus, paratype (arolium removed) (from Olmi 1984). E, F. E. rufus from China, paramere in ventral side (E) and dorsal view (F) (from Olmi 1995a). Scale bar 0.13 mm for A, 0.08 mm for B, 0.14 mm for C, 0.11 mm for D, E and F." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5278734" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5278734/files/figure.png" pageId="340" pageNumber="341">102C, D</figureCitation>
); segment 5 of protarsus with less than 15 medial lamellae (
<figureCitation id="98F21AC48F1AFE94496A5563FE47FD97" box="[346,482,591,615]" captionStart="PLATE 100" captionStartId="338.[151,233,1962,1985]" captionTargetBox="[182,1424,186,1921]" captionTargetId="figure-56@338.[151,1436,163,1977]" captionTargetPageId="338" captionText="PLATE 100. Echthrodelphax fairchildii. A, B. Female in dorsal view (A) and lateral view (B). Length 2.5 mm. C. Chela of female from Japan. Scale bar 0.16 mm for C. (From Olmi 1984)" figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5278728" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5278728/files/figure.png" pageId="340" pageNumber="341">Plates 100C</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="98F21AC48F1AFE9449C05563FDEAFD97" box="[496,591,591,615]" captionStart="PLATE 102" captionStartId="343.[151,234,1877,1900]" captionTargetBox="[220,1315,217,1819]" captionTargetId="figure-107@343.[166,1421,193,1856]" captionTargetPageId="343" captionText="PLATE 102. A, B, E, F. Male genitalia. C, D. Chelae. A. Echthrodelphax fairchildii from Hawaii (from Olmi 1984). B, C. E. laotianus from Thailand (from Olmi 1998e). C. E. laotianus, holotype (from Olmi 1984). D. E. rufus, paratype (arolium removed) (from Olmi 1984). E, F. E. rufus from China, paramere in ventral side (E) and dorsal view (F) (from Olmi 1995a). Scale bar 0.13 mm for A, 0.08 mm for B, 0.14 mm for C, 0.11 mm for D, E and F." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5278734" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5278734/files/figure.png" pageId="340" pageNumber="341">102C, D</figureCitation>
); tibial spurs 1/0/1. 
<emphasis id="32BDDA538F1AFE944B04557CFCC8FD98" box="[820,877,592,616]" italics="true" pageId="340" pageNumber="341">Male</emphasis>
: fully winged (
<figureCitation id="98F21AC48F1AFE944C2C5563FB1EFD97" box="[1052,1211,591,615]" captionStart="PLATE 101" captionStartId="339.[151,233,1968,1991]" captionTargetBox="[279,1268,185,1947]" captionTargetId="figure-39@339.[250,1337,153,1967]" captionTargetPageId="339" captionText="PLATE 101. Echthrodelphax fairchildii, males from Hawaii, Oahu, Ewa (from Olmi 1984). Length 1.8 mm. A. Dorsal view. B. Lateral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5278730" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5278730/files/figure.png" pageId="340" pageNumber="341">Plate 101A, B</figureCitation>
); head with distinct complete occipital carina; occiput concave; temple present; palpal formula 3/2, 4/2, 5/2, 5/3, or 6/3; tibial spurs 1/ 1/2.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="48D355CA8F1AFE9448F75597FE4EFD24" box="[199,491,699,724]" pageId="340" pageNumber="341" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="007606418F1AFE9448F75597FE4EFD24" blockId="340.[151,1436,411,796]" box="[199,491,699,724]" pageId="340" pageNumber="341">
<emphasis id="32BDDA538F1AFE9448F75597FEC5FD24" bold="true" box="[199,352,699,724]" pageId="340" pageNumber="341">Distribution.</emphasis>
Worldwide.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="48D355CA8F1AFE9448F755CCFC40FCEC" pageId="340" pageNumber="341" type="biology_ecology">
<paragraph id="007606418F1AFE9448F755CCFC99FD07" blockId="340.[151,1436,411,796]" box="[199,828,735,760]" pageId="340" pageNumber="341">
<emphasis id="32BDDA538F1AFE9448F755CCFEB4FD08" bold="true" box="[199,273,736,760]" pageId="340" pageNumber="341">Hosts.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="C7C97DC28F1AFE94492855F3FE01FD07" baseAuthorityName="Guglielmino &amp; Olmi" baseAuthorityYear="1997" box="[280,420,735,759]" class="Insecta" family="Delphacidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="340" pageNumber="341" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Delphacidae</taxonomicName>
(
<bibRefCitation id="64587BB08F1AFE94498255F3FD42FD07" author="Guglielmino &amp; Olmi" box="[434,743,735,759]" firstAuthor="Guglielmino" pageId="340" pageNumber="341" pagination="165 - 298" refId="ref360036" refString="Guglielmino, A. &amp; Olmi, M. (1997) A host-parasite catalog of world Dryinidae (Hymenoptera: Chrysidoidea). Contributions on Entomology, International, 2 (2), 165 - 298." type="journal article" year="1997">Guglielmino &amp; Olmi, 1997</bibRefCitation>
, 2006).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="007606418F1AFE9448F75428FC40FCEC" blockId="340.[151,1436,411,796]" box="[199,997,771,796]" pageId="340" pageNumber="341">
<emphasis id="32BDDA538F1AFE9448F75428FED1FCEC" bold="true" box="[199,372,771,796]" pageId="340" pageNumber="341">World species.</emphasis>
Twelve species are known, three in the 
<collectingRegion id="C20DC8A38F1AFE944B035428FC44FCEC" box="[819,993,772,796]" country="Democratic Republic of the Congo" name="Orientale" pageId="340" pageNumber="341">Oriental region</collectingRegion>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="48D355CA8F1AFE9448A75443FF51FC3E" pageId="340" pageNumber="341" type="multiple">
<paragraph id="007606418F1AFE9448A75443FED0FC79" blockId="340.[151,373,879,905]" box="[151,373,879,905]" pageId="340" pageNumber="341">
<emphasis id="32BDDA538F1AFE9448A75443FED0FC79" bold="true" box="[151,373,879,905]" pageId="340" pageNumber="341">Key to the species</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="007606418F1AFE9448A7549AFF51FC3E" blockId="340.[151,244,950,974]" box="[151,244,950,974]" pageId="340" pageNumber="341">Females</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="48D355CA8F1AFE9448A754D2FA39FB79" pageId="340" pageNumber="341" type="key">
<key id="745851708F1AFE9448A754D2FA39FB79" pageId="340" pageNumber="341">
<keyStep id="BB3D1EE48F1AFE9448A754D2FA39FBBE" pageId="340" pageNumber="341">
<paragraph id="007606418F1AFE9448A754D2FA39FBC1" blockId="340.[151,1436,1022,1161]" pageId="340" pageNumber="341">
<keyLead id="BB38A5748F1AFE9448A754D2FA39FBC1" pageId="340" pageNumber="341">
1. Fore wing with two brown transverse bands; body completely testaceous, with petiole black and metasoma darkened................................................................................................. 
<taxonomicName id="C7C97DC28F1AFE944D285330FA39FBC1" authority="Olmi" authorityName="Olmi 1984:" authorityYear="1157" box="[1304,1436,1052,1073]" class="Insecta" family="Dryinidae" genus="Echthrodelphax" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="340" pageNumber="341" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="rufus">
<emphasis id="32BDDA538F1AFE944D285330FAC1FBC1" box="[1304,1380,1052,1073]" italics="true" pageId="340" pageNumber="341">E. rufus</emphasis>
Olmi
</taxonomicName>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="007606418F1AFE9448A75315FA39FBBE" blockId="340.[151,1436,1022,1161]" box="[151,1436,1081,1102]" pageId="340" pageNumber="341">
<keyLead id="BB38A5748F1AFE9448A75315FA39FBBE" box="[151,1436,1081,1102]" pageId="340" pageNumber="341">- Fore wing hyaline, without dark transverse bands, or with one brown transverse band; mesosoma partly black............ 2</keyLead>
</paragraph>
</keyStep>
<keyStep id="BB3D1EE48F1AFE9448A7537AFA39FB79" pageId="340" pageNumber="341">
<paragraph id="007606418F1AFE9448A7537AFA39FB9B" blockId="340.[151,1436,1022,1161]" box="[151,1436,1110,1131]" pageId="340" pageNumber="341">
<keyLead id="BB38A5748F1AFE9448A7537AFA39FB9B" box="[151,1436,1110,1131]" pageId="340" pageNumber="341">
2. Scutum black; ocellar triangle usually without median keel, rarely with incomplete median keel..... 
<taxonomicName id="C7C97DC28F1AFE944C88537AFA39FB9B" authority="R. Perkins" authorityName="R. Perkins" authorityYear="1903" box="[1208,1436,1110,1131]" class="Insecta" family="Dryinidae" genus="Echthrodelphax" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="340" pageNumber="341" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="fairchildii">
<emphasis id="32BDDA538F1AFE944C88537AFA97FB9B" box="[1208,1330,1110,1131]" italics="true" pageId="340" pageNumber="341">E. fairchildii</emphasis>
R. Perkins
</taxonomicName>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="007606418F1AFE9448A75358FA39FB79" blockId="340.[151,1436,1022,1161]" box="[151,1436,1140,1161]" pageId="340" pageNumber="341">
<keyLead id="BB38A5748F1AFE9448A75358FA39FB79" box="[151,1436,1140,1161]" pageId="340" pageNumber="341">
- Scutum testaceous-reddish; ocellar triangle with complete median keel.............................. 
<taxonomicName id="C7C97DC28F1AFE944CC15358FA39FB79" authority="Olmi" authorityName="Olmi" box="[1265,1436,1140,1161]" class="Insecta" family="Dryinidae" genus="Bocchus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="340" pageNumber="341" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="laotianus">
<emphasis id="32BDDA538F1AFE944CC15358FAC1FB79" box="[1265,1380,1140,1161]" italics="true" pageId="340" pageNumber="341">E. laotianus</emphasis>
Olmi
</taxonomicName>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
</keyStep>
</key>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="48D355CA8F1AFE9448A75382FF7EFB36" box="[151,219,1198,1222]" pageId="340" pageNumber="341" type="multiple">
<paragraph id="007606418F1AFE9448A75382FF7EFB36" blockId="340.[151,219,1198,1222]" box="[151,219,1198,1222]" pageId="340" pageNumber="341">Males</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="48D355CA8F1AFE9448A753C3FA39FA67" pageId="340" pageNumber="341" type="key">
<key id="745851708F1AFE9448A753C3FA39FA67" pageId="340" pageNumber="341">
<keyStep id="BB3D1EE48F1AFE9448A753C3FA39FAAC" pageId="340" pageNumber="341">
<paragraph id="007606418F1AFE9448A753C3FA39FAD2" blockId="340.[151,1436,1263,1431]" pageId="340" pageNumber="341">
<keyLead id="BB38A5748F1AFE9448A753C3FA39FAD2" pageId="340" pageNumber="341">
1. Notauli complete, posteriorly joint; dorsal process of paramere pointed, short, distinctly developed (
<figureCitation id="98F21AC48F1AFE944CA953C3FAA2FAF4" box="[1177,1287,1263,1284]" captionStart="PLATE 102" captionStartId="343.[151,234,1877,1900]" captionTargetBox="[220,1315,217,1819]" captionTargetId="figure-107@343.[166,1421,193,1856]" captionTargetPageId="343" captionText="PLATE 102. A, B, E, F. Male genitalia. C, D. Chelae. A. Echthrodelphax fairchildii from Hawaii (from Olmi 1984). B, C. E. laotianus from Thailand (from Olmi 1998e). C. E. laotianus, holotype (from Olmi 1984). D. E. rufus, paratype (arolium removed) (from Olmi 1984). E, F. E. rufus from China, paramere in ventral side (E) and dorsal view (F) (from Olmi 1995a). Scale bar 0.13 mm for A, 0.08 mm for B, 0.14 mm for C, 0.11 mm for D, E and F." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5278734" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5278734/files/figure.png" pageId="340" pageNumber="341">Plate 102A</figureCitation>
); labial palpi 2- segmented......................................................................... 
<taxonomicName id="C7C97DC28F1AFE944C885221FA39FAD2" authority="R. Perkins" authorityName="R. Perkins" authorityYear="1903" box="[1208,1436,1293,1314]" class="Insecta" family="Dryinidae" genus="Echthrodelphax" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="340" pageNumber="341" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="fairchildii">
<emphasis id="32BDDA538F1AFE944C885221FA94FAD2" box="[1208,1329,1293,1314]" italics="true" pageId="340" pageNumber="341">E. fairchildii</emphasis>
R. Perkins
</taxonomicName>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="007606418F1AFE9448A75206FA39FAAC" blockId="340.[151,1436,1263,1431]" pageId="340" pageNumber="341">
<keyLead id="BB38A5748F1AFE9448A75206FA39FAAC" pageId="340" pageNumber="341">
- Notauli complete, posteriorly distinctly separated; dorsal process of paramere fold-shaped (
<figureCitation id="98F21AC48F1AFE944C6C5206FB58FACF" box="[1116,1277,1322,1343]" captionStart="PLATE 102" captionStartId="343.[151,234,1877,1900]" captionTargetBox="[220,1315,217,1819]" captionTargetId="figure-107@343.[166,1421,193,1856]" captionTargetPageId="343" captionText="PLATE 102. A, B, E, F. Male genitalia. C, D. Chelae. A. Echthrodelphax fairchildii from Hawaii (from Olmi 1984). B, C. E. laotianus from Thailand (from Olmi 1998e). C. E. laotianus, holotype (from Olmi 1984). D. E. rufus, paratype (arolium removed) (from Olmi 1984). E, F. E. rufus from China, paramere in ventral side (E) and dorsal view (F) (from Olmi 1995a). Scale bar 0.13 mm for A, 0.08 mm for B, 0.14 mm for C, 0.11 mm for D, E and F." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5278734" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5278734/files/figure.png" pageId="340" pageNumber="341">Plate 102B, E, F</figureCitation>
); labial palpi 3- segmented........................................................................................... 2
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
</keyStep>
<keyStep id="BB3D1EE48F1AFE9448A75249FA39FA67" pageId="340" pageNumber="341">
<paragraph id="007606418F1AFE9448A75249FA39FA8A" blockId="340.[151,1436,1263,1431]" box="[151,1436,1381,1402]" pageId="340" pageNumber="341">
<keyLead id="BB38A5748F1AFE9448A75249FA39FA8A" box="[151,1436,1381,1402]" pageId="340" pageNumber="341">
2. Fold of paramere strongly developed (
<figureCitation id="98F21AC48F1AFE944A615249FD18FA8A" box="[593,701,1381,1402]" captionStart="PLATE 102" captionStartId="343.[151,234,1877,1900]" captionTargetBox="[220,1315,217,1819]" captionTargetId="figure-107@343.[166,1421,193,1856]" captionTargetPageId="343" captionText="PLATE 102. A, B, E, F. Male genitalia. C, D. Chelae. A. Echthrodelphax fairchildii from Hawaii (from Olmi 1984). B, C. E. laotianus from Thailand (from Olmi 1998e). C. E. laotianus, holotype (from Olmi 1984). D. E. rufus, paratype (arolium removed) (from Olmi 1984). E, F. E. rufus from China, paramere in ventral side (E) and dorsal view (F) (from Olmi 1995a). Scale bar 0.13 mm for A, 0.08 mm for B, 0.14 mm for C, 0.11 mm for D, E and F." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5278734" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5278734/files/figure.png" pageId="340" pageNumber="341">Plate 102B</figureCitation>
); paramere without sense organs (
<figureCitation id="98F21AC48F1AFE944C355249FBD5FA8A" box="[1029,1136,1381,1402]" captionStart="PLATE 102" captionStartId="343.[151,234,1877,1900]" captionTargetBox="[220,1315,217,1819]" captionTargetId="figure-107@343.[166,1421,193,1856]" captionTargetPageId="343" captionText="PLATE 102. A, B, E, F. Male genitalia. C, D. Chelae. A. Echthrodelphax fairchildii from Hawaii (from Olmi 1984). B, C. E. laotianus from Thailand (from Olmi 1998e). C. E. laotianus, holotype (from Olmi 1984). D. E. rufus, paratype (arolium removed) (from Olmi 1984). E, F. E. rufus from China, paramere in ventral side (E) and dorsal view (F) (from Olmi 1995a). Scale bar 0.13 mm for A, 0.08 mm for B, 0.14 mm for C, 0.11 mm for D, E and F." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5278734" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5278734/files/figure.png" pageId="340" pageNumber="341">Plate 102B</figureCitation>
).......... 
<taxonomicName id="C7C97DC28F1AFE944CC15249FA39FA8A" authority="Olmi" authorityName="Olmi" box="[1265,1436,1381,1402]" class="Insecta" family="Dryinidae" genus="Bocchus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="340" pageNumber="341" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="laotianus">
<emphasis id="32BDDA538F1AFE944CC15249FAC1FA8A" box="[1265,1380,1381,1402]" italics="true" pageId="340" pageNumber="341">E. laotianus</emphasis>
Olmi
</taxonomicName>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="007606418F1AFE9448A752AEFA39FA67" blockId="340.[151,1436,1263,1431]" box="[151,1436,1410,1431]" pageId="340" pageNumber="341">
